Detailed Description

Central item type management class.

It contains a map of all item types, accessible via find_template. Those item types are loaded from json via the load_* functions.

It also contains all item groups that are used to spawn items.

You usually use the single global instance item_controller.

Like above, but the above loads data from several members of the object, this function assume the given array is the "entries" member of the item group.

For each element in the array, Item_factory::add_entry is called.

Assuming the input array looks like [ x, y, z ], this function loads it like the above would load this object:

{
"subtype": "depends on is_collection parameter",
"id": "identifier",
"entries": [ x, y, z ]
}

Note that each entry in the array has to be a JSON object. The other function above can also load data from arrays of strings, where the strings are item or group ids.

Load a item group from json.

It differs from the other load_item_group function as it uses the ident and subtype given as parameter and does not look up those things in the json data (the json object here does not need to have them). This is intended for inline definitions of item groups, e.g. in monster death drops: the item group there is embedded into the monster type definition.

Parameters
jsobjThe json object to load from.
group_idThe ident of the item that is to be loaded.
subtypeThe type of the item group, either "collection", "distribution" or "old" ("old" is a distribution, too).
Exceptions
JsonErrorif the json object contains invalid data.
